snippet.description: I guess you could say he was suffering from blue...[animorphs into a volleyball]...balls.

snippet.title: Belated Mother's Day
snippet.description: It's a trick that works surprisingly often. But getting the melons past grocery store security is often the hardest part, particularly if you have birthing hips and a desperate look in your eyes.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 5/7 - 5/11
snippet.description: We're back-to-basics with our format this week, but we DO answer an honest question about comics, set up a very-much-for-real plan to mail a fan a cookie, and debate the merits of modern self-promotion on YouTube! Also includes a philosophical discussion about bananas that is sure to offend.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #185
snippet.description: 5sf Assembles to save the fool in the pool but it turns out to be a dating trap when President Kelsey orders a them to play ski-ball with their lives.

snippet.title: What Really Happens When You Die
snippet.description: Life is but a quarter, plunked into the coin slot of fate. We know not how far we'll fly when our judgment day comes, nor if our aim shall be true. But either way, we'll know the ticket payout is a ripoff compared to the Whack-a-Mole machine in the other corner of the universe.

snippet.title: President Kelsey
snippet.description: Twelve people camped outside the White House, protesting the arrest. But they were all ugly losers, so the local authorities had no trouble hosing them out.

snippet.title: The Dating Trap
snippet.description: Contestants leave with lovely parting gifts, including a year's supply of Strawberry Quik, a trip to Space Camp, and a pair of L.A. Lights. All for your fucking money-suck of a kid, of course.

snippet.title: The Fool in the Pool
snippet.description: Unsure of how else to tell him he had a cheating girlfriend, his close friends bought him a pair of inflatable water wings so he'd stay above water long enough to hear of the infidelities himself. Sadly, his powerful legs still found a way to dive to the floor, where he could retrieve sunken pool toys in blissful ignorance.

snippet.title: 5SF Assemble!
snippet.description: This was filmed on a budget of $130.53, but the opening internet grosses are our highest-ever. So we should make our money back in 5 years.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #184
snippet.description: A Hollywood Waitress' best friend plays matchmaker and sets her up with a Therapist who has a fetish for 3-D Food and punching pregnant women in the belly.

snippet.title: Matchmaker
snippet.description: If you can't even be your own wingman through a ripped interdimensional portal, you and your penis should probably just take some time off to think about life.

snippet.title: Dream Therapy
snippet.description: On the plus side, that was her last free session before she'd have to start paying regular visitation fees, so this kinda all worked out in the finish. "Finish" being the entire world.

snippet.title: Hollywood Waitress
snippet.description: Sometimes they sprinkle a little too much desperation on it, but it's hard to look them in the eyes and make them take it back to the kitchen. Still, there's a diner on Melrose that does it just right, with a delicious side of Actual Talent That You Should Totally Pursue Instead, It'll Make You Way Way Happier.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 4/23 - 4/27
snippet.description: This week, we read comments from some of our main site regulars (y'know, over at 5secondfilms.com, where you can get the newest 5sf every day). No hard feelings, we hope!

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #183
snippet.description:
On prom night a missile fails to launch, but the young man turns this learning tower into a new mission of blue shazaaming.

snippet.title: Shazaam: The Lazy Genie
snippet.description: What's the first thing that comes to mind when you hear the name Shazaam? You're thinking about the Shaq movie "Kazaam" aren't you? Turn around. Boom. There's the VHS for it, right behind you. Two wishes left, by the way.

snippet.title: New Mission
snippet.description: New Mission Force is located right across the street from Impossible Mission Force, in a bald-faced attempt to steal some of their business. Alas, not even hiring a teenager to flip a big arrow sign seems to make a dent in their competition.

snippet.title: The Leaning Tower of Terror
snippet.description: This is what happens when the architect accidentally shifts his blueprints 15 degrees clockwise during construction.

snippet.title: Houston Has A Problem
snippet.description: The Apollo program was soon suspended, despite Ted's Puckish insistence that the review board's "mommas" were suspended instead. At a loss for a comeback, the chairman just put Ted in a headlock and gave him a noogie until he agreed not to be a dumbass anymore.

snippet.title: Noey And Vivek 4eva
snippet.description: So not too long ago, a 5sf fan named Vivek e-mailed us (really) to see if there was some way we could help him ask a girl named Noey to prom. Vivek, we hope this helps. Also, any resemblance to Noey's actual dad is purely coincidental.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 4/16 - 4/20
snippet.description:
More flags, more fun! Wait, that's Six Flags' slogan, not an introduction to this week's comments video! Oh well, there's fun to be had nonetheless, from a bald Worley to a disappearing Alec & Paul, a fight over the word "Bluebird" and an insane explosion of hate speech from an obvious troll!

Next week, we'll only be taking comments from our home site at 5secondfilms.com. Y'know, the URL that's in the opening credits of every single one of our 5sfs! So if you want a chance to be heard, come on over!

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #182

snippet.title: April 20th
snippet.description: Before you pro-legalization guys scream "false equivalency," seriously just give heroin a shot. We recommend pilfering it from the bottom of an unconscious hooker's boot somewhere in the depths of K-Town.

snippet.title: Loverboy
snippet.description: Clearly, somebody read "The Game" and thought the tips were applying to girls so vapid and dull that they were literally mannequin heads. Or at least, that's the only explanation I could understand.

snippet.title: Useless Fact Cowboy: Spring Break Edition
snippet.description: He could also show you how to surf on the back of a sea otter. But you're not ready for that useless information yet, you stupid youngling.

snippet.title: Brothers In Arms
snippet.description: They shared a passion for doing the same thing they always do, six times a day at minimum, no matter what obstacle stands in their way. A sweet, sacred passion.

snippet.title: Fantasy Lover
snippet.description: His constant insistence that it would be "really hot if she grew a goatee" became something of a roadblock in their relationship. When she walked in to find the red wig on a cardboard cutout head of the dude from Sugar Ray, she knew it was all over.
